<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="for-prep">for <strong><em>prep</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /fə(r)/    美 /fər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>对于；供；适合于：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>books for children 
儿童读物</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Here is a letter for you. 
这儿有你一封信。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It's time for class.
上课时间到了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>为了：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Are you learning English for pleasure or for your work?
你学英语是出于兴趣还是为了工作?</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>达；计：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We have stayed here for two months.
我们已在这里待了两个月了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>For miles and miles you see nothing but trees.
绵延数英里，除了树你什么也看不到。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>往；向：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Is this train for Dalian? 
这是开往大连的火车吗？</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>至于；就…而言：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is very cold for October.
十月里这样的天气真够冷的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>For a beginner he drives well.
就初学者来说，他开得不错。</p></div>

<h4 id="6">6.★ <strong>由于；因为：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If it weren't for Dad, I wouldn't be where I am today.
要不是因为父亲，我就不会有今天。</p><footer>2017天津</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The taxi driver was fined for speeding.
那个出租车司机因超速被罚款。</p></div>

<h4 id="7">7.★ <strong>换：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>change for another 
换另一个</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He paid forty yuan for the book.
他花40元钱买了这本书。</p></div>

<h4 id="8">8.★ <strong>赞成；拥护；有利于：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Are you for or against the proposal?
你赞成还是反对这个建议？</p></div>

<h4 id="9">9.★ <strong>代；替；代表：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Mr Jackson attended the meeting for our school.
杰克逊先生代表我校参加了会议。</p></div>

<h4 id="10">10.★ <strong>在：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>an appointment for Monday 
星期一的约会</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— Good morning, Mr. Lee's offi ce.
— Good morning. I'd like to make an appointment<strong><em>_</em></strong>_next Wednesday afternoon.  （2018 北京改）  </li>
<li>We have more time with after-school activities.  （2014 全国 改错）  </li>
<li>Nothing is so easy as <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ parents to raise their expectations of their children too high.  （2012 福建改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. for  2. with → for  3. for  </p></div>